<p>

<i>Family Policy</i> is an eight-page publication issued six times a year. 
By taking an in-depth look at research trends and policy initiatives 
currently being debated in the public arena, it offers detailed advice to 
policy makers interested in tackling some of our nation's most serious 
social problems.

<p>

<a href="/townhall/FRC/subscribe/subscribe.html.cgi">Subscribe</a> 
to our <i>Family Policy</i> mailing list so that you will receive 
E-Mail notification each time a new issue is available. This will 
prevent you from having to frequently check back for new issues.

