<P>
<h2>December's Contents</h2>
<HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=50%>
</center>
<P><P>

<b>12/29/95</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="/heritage/p_review/jan96/wepeo.html">"100 Gallon Heroes,"</a> the first installment of <i>Policy Review</i>'s new series, <i>We the People:  A Chonicle of American Generosity</i>.
<li>Read Wesley Pruden's comments on the <a href="/wash_times/pruden1225.html">Republican Congressional Froshmen</a>.
<li>Pressure is mounting on President Clinton to sign the <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c95l29.html">partial-birth abortion ban</a>; read about it in Gary Bauer's daily radio commentary.
<li>Michael Fumento dispells the <a href="/townhall/columnists/fume1228.html">Love Canal myth</a> that has enshrouded the EPA for years.
<li>Get your <a href="/atr/">Tax Fact of the Day</a> at Americans for Tax Reform.
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/chav1228.html">Kudos to GOP Congress</a> in Linda Chavez's latest column.
<li>England's <a href="/nationalreview/31dec95/onthrgt.htm">"pot war"</a> rages on, and William F. Buckley brings you the story.
<li>"Behind the Headlines" with F.R. Duplantier:  <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl1229.html">"Illiteracy and Deliquency."</a>

</ul>
<b>12/28/95</b>
<ul>
<li>Kate O'Beirne predicts a less hectic Second Session, in <a href="/nationalreview/31dec95/capitol.htm">"Bread and Circuses,"</a> from <i>National Review</i>.
<li>Read <i><a href="/heritage/p_review/jan96/coats.html">Can Congress
 Revive Civil Society</a></i>, by Senator Dan Coats, with responses by 
Gertrude Himmelfarb, Don Eberly, and David Boaz in the new <I>Policy Review</i>.
<li>What is <a href="/yaf/pres-m.html">YAF</a>?
<li>CAGW analyzes results of the <a href="/govt-waste/CapitolHill/PressReleases/megapr.html">December Megapoll</a> and finds that taxpayers know the truth about the GOP budget plan.
<li>Read Suzanne Fields's column on the <a href="/wash_times/fields1225.html">comback of Jane Austen</a>.
<li>Have you heard the hilarious <a href="http://www.nashville.net/~shanklin/">spoofs of President Clinton</a> on the Rush Limbaugh radio program? Check out comedian Paul Shanklin's site to download some songs and skits, and find out how to order a CD full of his material.
</ul>
<b>12/27/95</b>
<ul>
<li>Do carry the highest tax burden in the U.S.?  Find out in ATR's <a href="/atr/1.html">Tax Fact of The Day</a>.
<li>The December 31, 1995 issue of <i><a href="/nationalreview/31dec95/contents.html">National Review</a></i> has arrived!
<li>The new edition of the <i><a href="/wash_times/">Washington Times National Weekly</a></i> is now available.
<li>Find out what's happening on the Hill this week in FRC's <a href="/townhall/FRC/hotline/hotline.html">Legislative Hotline</a>.
<li>New columns from F.R. Duplantier:
<ul>
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl1227.html">"Bosnia"</a>
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl1226.html">"Secular Humanism"</a>
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl1225.html">"Christmas Verse"</a>

</ul>
</ul>
<b>12/22/95</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/fume1221.html">"The Government's Legal Theft Racket,"</a> by Michael Fumento.
<li>Get ATR's <a href="/atr/1.html">Tax Fact of the Day.</a>
<li>Should taxpayers pay for people to shop?  Republican Congressional leaders seem to.  Find out more in ACU's <a href="/conservative/lout1223.html">Latest Republican Outrage.</a>
<li>A new column from F.R. Duplantier, <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl1222.html">"Founding Fathers."</a>
<li>Pete du Pont discusses the intracacies of the Federal Reserve in <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupo1220.html">"Maintaining the Value of the Dollar."</a>
<li>Freedom <i>of</i> versus freedom <i>from</i> religion is the topic of Linda Chavez's <a href="/townhall/columnists/chav1221.html">"Call It A Miracle."</a> 
<li>CAGW's Thomas Schatz reveals: A child born today will pay <a href="/townhall/columnists/scha1221.html">$187,000 in taxes</a> over a lifetime just to pay his or her share of the interest on the national debt.
<li>New commentary from the Heritage foundation:
<ul>
<li>Robert E. Moffit's <a href="/heritage/commentary/op-rm1.html">"Tax Credit Could Pay for College"</a>
<li><a href="/heritage/commentary/op-wb1.html">"Not Just a Rich Man's Issue,"</a> by William Beach.
</ul>
<li>Three new columns from ACU's Bill Pascoe:
<ul>
<li><a href="/conservative/columnists/pasc1223.html">Jockeying for the Cultural Conservatives</a>
<li><a href="/conservative/columnists/pasc1222.html">No Taxpayer-Paid Vacations for Furloughed Federal Employees</a>
<li><A href="/conservative/columnists/pasc1221.html">Dole Reverses Field, Saves Himself ...For Now</a>
</ul>
</ul>
