<h2>The <i>Right</i> Numbers</h2>Compiled from the 1990 Long Form Census information<p>
<h3>Top Ten Stats for the Week of November 27</h3></center>

<hr><P>

<b>1. Educational attainment</b>, persons 25 years and over:<p><center>		Graduated from High School: 	<br>1980: 67%<br>						1993: 80%<p>		Graduated from College:<br>		1980: 16%<br>						1993: 22%<br><p></center>Source: USA Statistics in Brief, Part 2. <i>1994 Statistical Abstract</i>, U.S. Bureau of the Census.<p><b>2.</b>     Average sentence and percent served for <b>violent state prisoners</b>:<p><center>		Average sentence, 1992-1994: 		10 years<br>		Percentage of sentence served, 1994:  	48%
</center><p>
Source: "State Inmates, 1992-1994: Violent Offenders in State Prison: Sentences and Time Served," <i>Selected Findings</i>, Bureau of Justice Statistics, July 1995 
<p>
<b>3.</b>      Based on a 1991 survey of state prisoners, among <b>prisoners with a life sentence</b>:	<p><center>	69% said they expected to be released<br>		13% said they would never be released
</center><p>Source: <I> Ibid.</i><p><b>4.</b> Percent of Americans over <b>65</b> living on more than <b>$15,000 a year</b>:<p><center>		1990: 30%</center><p>Source: 1990 Census.<p><b>5.  Women in Labor force</b> (in Millions):<p>
<pre>
Year      Single       Married       Divorced/Widowed/Separated
1970	   7	      18.4	                5.9
1980	   11.2	      24.9	                8.8
1990	   14	      31	               11.2
</pre><p>Source: <i>Statistical Abstract of the United States, 1994</i>. Table #626.<p>
<b>6.</b>  Employment in the <b>Agriculture Industry</b> by Thousands:<p><center>1970   3,463<br>1980   3,364<br>1985   3,179<br>1990   3,186<br></center><p>Source: <i>Statistical Abstract of the United States, 1994</i>.  Table #641.
<p>
<b>7.  Unemployment Rates</b>:
<p><center>
1975  8.5<br>
1980  7.1<br>
1985  7.2<br>
1990  7.4<br>
1993  6.8<br>
</center><p>
Source: <i>Statistical Abstract of the United States, 1994</i>.  Table#648.
<p>
<b>8.  Average Hourly Earnings</b>  in Current Dollars:
<p><center>
1980  $6.66<br>
1985  $8.57<br>
1990  $10.01<br>
1992  $10.58<br>
1993  $10.83<br>
</center><p>
Source: <i>Statistical Abstract of the United States, 1994</i>.  Table #661.   

<p>
<b>9.</b> Percentage of <b>popular vote for President</b>:
		<p><center>
